theorem Topology.closure_interior_union_eq_union_closures
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B)) =
      closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  -- First, rewrite `interior (A ∪ B)` in terms of `interior A` and `interior B`.
  have h : interior (A ∪ B) = interior A ∪ interior B := interior_union
  -- Apply the existing lemma about the closure of a union of interiors.
  simpa [h] using
    (Topology.closure_union_interiors_eq (X := X) (A := A) (B := B))

theorem interior_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A ∪ B) = interior (A ∪ B) := rfl
